Arsenal legend, Paul Merson, has predicted outcomes of some of this weekend’s Premier League matches. His predictions for the Premier League fixtures include Chelsea’s clash against Tottenham. Thomas Tuchel’s side go up against Tottenham on Sunday at Stamford Bridge and Merson is backing the west London side to win 2-0 this weekend. For Manchester United, Ralf Rangnick’s men face off against West Ham at Old Trafford on Saturday, with both sides vying for the top four. And Arsenal hero Merson is expecting West Ham to cause ‘problems’ for United in the final third and thinks the match will end in a 1-1 draw. Merson’s Premier League predictions, according to Metro: Watford 2-0 Norwich Everton 1-2 Aston Villa Brentford 0-2 Wolves Leeds 2-1 Newcastle Man Utd 1-1 West Ham Southampton 1-0 Man City Crystal Palace 1-1 Liverpool Arsenal 3-0 Burnley Leicester 2-2 Brighton Chelsea 2-0 Spurs.